1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,610
A young fiction writer talked with me recently about her writing ambitions.

2
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:08,529
The name of one of the top writers in her field came up.

3
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:17,090
Oh, she said, Mr. X is a wonderful writer, but, of course, I can't be nearly as successful as he is.

4
00:00:17,520 --> 00:00:22,450
Her attitude disappointed me very much, because I know the writer mentioned.

5
00:00:22,640 --> 00:00:29,809
He is not super-intelligent nor super-perceptive, nor super-anything else except super-confident.

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,409
He believes he is among the best, and so he acts and performs the best.

7
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:43,490
It is well to respect the leader, learn from him, observe him, study him, but don't worship him.

8
00:00:43,760 --> 00:00:45,890
Believe you can surpass.

9
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:47,970
Believe you can go beyond.

10
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:53,970
Those who harbor the second-best attitude are invariably second-best doers.

11
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,809
Look at it this way.

12
00:00:56,080 --> 00:01:00,610
Belief is the thermostat that regulates what we accomplish in life.

13
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,929
Study the fellow who is shuffling down there in mediocrity.

14
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:08,770
He believes he is worth little, so he receives little.

15
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:12,529
He believes he can't do big things, and he doesn't.

16
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:18,370
He believes he is unimportant, so everything he does has an unimportant mark.

17
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:26,370
As time goes by, lack of belief in himself shows through in the way the fellow talks, walks, acts.

18
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:34,450
Unless he readjusts his thermostat forward, he shrinks, grows smaller and smaller in his own estimation.

19
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:42,210
And since others see in us what we see in ourselves, he grows smaller in the estimation of the people around him.

20
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:46,929
Now, look across the way at the person who is advancing forward.

21
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:50,850
He believes he is worth much, and he receives much.

22
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:55,490
He believes he can handle big, difficult assignments, and he does.

23
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:01,490
Everything he does, the way he handles himself with people, his character, his thoughts,

24
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:05,090
his viewpoints, all say, here is a professional.

25
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:07,330
He is an important person.

26
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:11,090
A person is a product of his own thoughts.

27
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,610
Believe big.

28
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:15,090
Adjust your thermostat forward.

29
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:21,010
Launch your success offensive with honest, sincere belief that you can succeed.

30
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,569
Believe big and grow big.

